1
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:34,940
I'm worried.

2
00:00:37,050 --> 00:00:41,310
Just as much as you worry
about me and console me,

3
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:43,540
I wish...

4
00:00:44,790 --> 00:00:46,350
to do so for you too.

5
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:49,100
Does that mean...

6
00:00:51,260 --> 00:00:53,880
I've become a bit more...

7
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,630
special to you...

8
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:58,650
than before?

9
00:01:02,270 --> 00:01:03,360
Yes.

10
00:01:15,350 --> 00:01:16,580
Yes, this is Kwon Jung Rok.

11
00:01:17,850 --> 00:01:19,010
Hello, Judge.

12
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:22,820
You don't need to send me
the sentencing report.

13
00:01:23,390 --> 00:01:24,410
Okay.

14
00:01:35,370 --> 00:01:38,410
Anyway, thank you for
working hard to help me...

15
00:01:38,410 --> 00:01:39,590
win the difficult trial.

16
00:01:40,210 --> 00:01:41,770
You should get some rest for tomorrow.

17
00:01:48,820 --> 00:01:49,840
Wait.

18
00:01:50,890 --> 00:01:52,480
"For tomorrow"?

19
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,130
Is tomorrow a special day or something?

20
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:00,550
Is he going to ask me out?

21
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:07,760
He probably would've asked me out
if he didn't get a call earlier.

22
00:02:10,810 --> 00:02:12,680
My gosh!

23
00:02:13,170 --> 00:02:16,170
Goodness me. He'll ask me out tomorrow.

24
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:20,420
(Episode 7)

25
00:02:24,490 --> 00:02:26,090
- Good morning!
- Good morning.

26
00:02:26,090 --> 00:02:27,590
- Hello.
- Good morning.

27
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,700
Good morning!

28
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,330
Did something good happen to her?

29
00:02:32,730 --> 00:02:34,090
I don't know.

30
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:40,000
Did he go somewhere?

31
00:02:43,570 --> 00:02:44,630
What's with the flowers?

32
00:02:46,340 --> 00:02:48,250
Are they from Mr. Kwon?

33
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:25,780
"The cold that didn't seem to
want to back off finally did,"

34
00:03:26,610 --> 00:03:29,640
"and warm spring days are drawing near."

35
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:33,190
Gosh, can he be any more romantic?

36
00:03:34,890 --> 00:03:37,690
"Although it's nothing grand,"

37
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:40,550
"the gift was chosen from the heart,"

38
00:03:40,730 --> 00:03:43,730
"so I hope you willingly accept it."

39
00:03:44,070 --> 00:03:47,100
What do you mean it's nothing grand?
It couldn't be more precious!

40
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:52,590
"The battle was tough,
but you never gave up."

41
00:03:52,610 --> 00:03:55,980
"That's why she wasn't made a scapegoat."

42
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:57,930
A scapegoat?

43
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:03,530
"Thank you for taking Im Yun Hee's case."

44
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:05,830
"From President Lee Yeong Ok of
the Korean Women's Association."

45
00:04:10,990 --> 00:04:12,460
Oh, you're here.

46
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:15,890
- These...
- The flowers?

47
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,760
The Korean Women's Association sent them.

48
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:19,270
I don't like flowers,

49
00:04:19,280 --> 00:04:21,160
so I put them here for you to enjoy.

50
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:25,230
I see.

51
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:30,600
Mr. Yeon's calling everyone
to go over their cases.

52
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:31,900
All right.

53
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:33,870
Let's get ready and head out.

54
00:04:43,790 --> 00:04:45,700
Before we begin the briefing,

55
00:04:45,830 --> 00:04:48,350
let's give a round of applause to Mr. Kwon,

56
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,900
the hope...

57
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:52,150
and gem of our law firm,

58
00:04:52,170 --> 00:04:54,040
for successfully winning
the Im Yun Hee Case.

59
00:04:57,070 --> 00:04:59,150
That's enough, everyone. Thank you.

60
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,250
There's no reason to be embarrassed.

61
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,950
Although, that's what
makes you so charming.

62
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:06,560
Then let's get on with the briefing.

63
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:10,040
Our law firm is taking
on the Sangji-dong Case.

64
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:11,860
Since it's a big case,

65
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:15,490
Mr. Kwon will brief us
and we'll share ideas.

66
00:05:15,690 --> 00:05:16,740
Sure.

67
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:23,560
Before I begin, let me show
you the defendant's photo.

68
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:28,730
What's going on?

69
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,460
Why is there a photo of Yun Seo,
the universe's goddess?

70
00:05:31,670 --> 00:05:34,370
What crime did she commit?

71
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,530
Her crimes?

72
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:40,620
She committed theft by stealing my heart.

73
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:44,470
She committed assault by
blinding me with her beauty.

74
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:49,390
She even committed attempted murder
by making me break my heart...

75
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:50,410
if I don't see her even for a day.

76
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:53,820
I argue Jin Sim receives
life imprisonment...

77
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:56,680
and be with me for the rest of my life.

78
00:05:58,200 --> 00:05:59,320
Jin Sim,

79
00:05:59,570 --> 00:06:01,200
will you go out with me?

80
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:05,220
Take me. Put me in cuffs.
Take me right away!

81
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:07,430
Ms. Oh?

82
00:06:08,710 --> 00:06:10,010
What are you doing?

83
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:13,400
What is this?

84
00:06:17,590 --> 00:06:18,670
(Sangji-dong Parricide Case)

85
00:06:25,060 --> 00:06:27,070
Him! He will...

86
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:29,480
be imprisoned for sure.

87
00:06:30,370 --> 00:06:32,510
Mr. Kwon will do his best...

88
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,200
to make that happen.

89
00:06:39,810 --> 00:06:42,230
Ms. Oh, you can be quite silly at times.

90
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:44,550
That's what makes her so charming.

91
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:47,850
Her looks are stunning,
but she has a whimsical side.

92
00:06:48,880 --> 00:06:51,240
Thank you for thinking of me so nicely.

93
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:55,010
Anyway, he's a bad man.

94
00:06:57,260 --> 00:06:59,270
Let me begin the briefing then.

95
00:07:05,470 --> 00:07:08,770
Are you insane? What's wrong with you?

96
00:07:14,610 --> 00:07:16,350
Get a grip on yourself.

97
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:19,540
You're an actress,
so wait for him elegantly.

98
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:20,840
Be hard-to-get.

99
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,650
It's already 6pm.

100
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:45,410
Gosh, is that a heart?

101
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:47,780
Is he sending it my way?

102
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:57,590
He's telling me how he feels
by small, trivial gestures.

103
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:06,610
Was he just wiping the glass?

104
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:17,640
I've been too busy to notice,
but the office is a mess.

105
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:20,860
I guess I should complain to the cleaners.

106
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:24,220
I'll do that, so don't worry about it.

107
00:08:25,150 --> 00:08:26,170
Good night.

108
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:27,440
Wait.

109
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:32,690
Is that it?

110
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:36,100
Don't you have anything else to say?

111
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:38,190
- Sorry?
- Whatever.

112
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:40,390
It's nothing.

113
00:08:46,070 --> 00:08:48,010
I'll head home first then.

114
00:09:16,060 --> 00:09:18,010
I dolled myself up today for nothing.

115
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:22,600
You're doing it again.

116
00:09:23,070 --> 00:09:24,700
You promised yourself that you'd wait.

117
00:09:25,610 --> 00:09:28,160
Now, turn on the hard-to-get actress mode.

118
00:09:38,380 --> 00:09:42,660
♫ <i>One step at a time</i> ♫

119
00:09:42,660 --> 00:09:45,720
I'll nonchalantly wait for him.

120
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:49,550
♫ <i>Too much for your mind </i> ♫

121
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:56,110
♫ <i>I was only being kind</i> ♫

122
00:09:56,110 --> 00:09:58,940
♫ <i>There's no need to analyze</i> ♫

123
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:00,440
Nonchalantly.

124
00:10:11,690 --> 00:10:13,630
(Secretary Oh Jin Sim)

125
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:21,380
- Jin Sim...
- I can't wait.

126
00:10:21,930 --> 00:10:25,300
- Sorry?
- I can't wait any longer.

127
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,440
I won't play hard-to-get.

128
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:31,080
I'd rather just say
everything that's on my mind.

129
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:35,040
I've been going insane...

130
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:38,580
waiting for you to ask me out.

131
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:42,120
- What do you mean?
- Do you not want to?

132
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,480
Okay, fine.

133
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:46,580
I'll make the first move then.

134
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,610
My gosh. Now that I have to say it...

135
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:53,690
Hold on a second.

136
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:04,960
I like you, Mr. Kwon.

137
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:11,830
Do you remember what I told you?

138
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:15,440
I said I had...

139
00:11:16,020 --> 00:11:18,030
something to tell you.

140
00:11:18,050 --> 00:11:20,090
I couldn't say it now,

141
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:24,030
but I promised to tell you someday.

142
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:25,150
Do you remember that?

143
00:11:26,690 --> 00:11:27,960
My gosh.

144
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:31,040
Anyway, that's...

145
00:11:31,830 --> 00:11:33,200
I love you.

146
00:11:33,370 --> 00:11:34,700
You see...

147
00:11:37,070 --> 00:11:39,690
You have taken a spot...

148
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:41,880
in my heart.

149
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:43,470
I mean...

150
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:48,140
In my heart that is clean, clear, and pure,

151
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:53,530
you came and made a place for yourself.

152
00:11:53,650 --> 00:11:55,560
That's what I mean.

153
00:11:58,630 --> 00:11:59,990
That's why...

154
00:12:01,130 --> 00:12:03,890
when you said last night...

155
00:12:04,230 --> 00:12:06,950
that I've become a bit more special to you,

156
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:10,510
I felt so happy.

157
00:12:11,970 --> 00:12:16,670
And I waited all day for
you to say something else.

158
00:12:18,810 --> 00:12:21,680
But how could you humiliate me like that?

159
00:12:22,420 --> 00:12:24,050
I'm Oh Yun Seo!

160
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:28,620
- Mr. Kwon, you're so mean!
- Jin Sim.

161
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:32,580
Jin Sim?

162
00:12:48,980 --> 00:12:50,140
What are you doing?

163
00:12:51,450 --> 00:12:52,980
What's the matter? Is something wrong?

164
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,730
Is the case you're working
on giving you trouble again?

165
00:12:58,790 --> 00:12:59,910
Forget it.

166
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:05,510
What's the matter with him? Gosh.

167
00:13:07,330 --> 00:13:09,230
I'll state the facts only,
so listen carefully.

168
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:11,580
A man started to develop
feelings for a woman.

169
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:15,450
So he told her,
"You've become a special person to me."

170
00:13:15,770 --> 00:13:16,790
This is what he said.

171
00:13:18,270 --> 00:13:21,100
The man thought that would be enough.

172
00:13:21,380 --> 00:13:24,880
He thought they could take things slow,
since they liked each other.

173
00:13:25,010 --> 00:13:26,820
But the woman had different thoughts.

174
00:13:27,950 --> 00:13:31,120
She wanted him to make the next move,
but when he didn't,

175
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,240
she got extremely angry.

176
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,260
Is this really the man's fault?

177
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:41,600
Is this really about a case? Not you?

178
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:42,750
It's not about me!

179
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:45,350
- It's about my client.
- You've got to be kidding me.

180
00:13:46,330 --> 00:13:48,620
Did you set up a dating
agency or something?

181
00:13:49,570 --> 00:13:50,800
My goodness.

182
00:13:52,070 --> 00:13:53,880
Forget it. It's no use asking you.

183
00:13:55,780 --> 00:13:57,010
It's not the man's fault.

184
00:13:57,580 --> 00:13:59,080
What you said isn't actually wrong.

185
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,520
- Right?
- Still,

186
00:14:05,050 --> 00:14:06,790
I'd like to side with the woman.

187
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:11,960
Who on earth takes dating so
logically like you just said?

188
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,300
You normally get to know
each other as you date.

189
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:16,100
The man already made the first move.

190
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:18,990
He said something crucial,
by saying she was special.

191
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:22,200
But if he cuts her off suddenly,
who would like that?

192
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:27,860
You still don't understand?

193
00:14:28,380 --> 00:14:30,280
Listen. Let's say you're at a trial.

194
00:14:30,850 --> 00:14:34,930
"Your Honor, considering all
the circumstantial evidence,"

195
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:37,260
"the defendant did not behave
like that purposely, and..."

196
00:14:37,790 --> 00:14:39,790
"his alibi on the day of the
incident has been confirmed."

197
00:14:39,820 --> 00:14:40,940
"Therefore, I..."

198
00:14:44,060 --> 00:14:45,320
How would you feel if the
trial ends like this?

199
00:14:45,890 --> 00:14:47,590
- It feels uncomfortable.
- Right?

200
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:51,240
You said all the important words,
but there is no conclusion.

201
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:52,450
That's what you...

202
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:58,110
No, your client has done...

203
00:14:58,110 --> 00:14:59,810
to that woman. Okay?

204
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:17,630
Jin Sim, I'm sorry.

205
00:15:18,130 --> 00:15:20,580
I thought we were in the stage
of getting to know each other.

206
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:30,990
Jin Sim, I was inconsiderate.

207
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:33,080
Please forgive me, and be my...

208
00:15:38,610 --> 00:15:41,540
Jin Sim, let's meet tomorrow and talk.

209
00:15:50,860 --> 00:15:52,530
Yes, what is it this time?

210
00:15:53,530 --> 00:15:57,610
Well, there's something you
should tell your client.

211
00:15:57,970 --> 00:15:59,710
He should ask her out soon,

212
00:15:59,730 --> 00:16:03,340
and prepare flowers,
or something small and shiny.

213
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:05,960
He should prepare anything that she likes.

214
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,080
- What?
- Going empty-handed...

215
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,240
when he asks her out...

216
00:16:11,410 --> 00:16:14,310
is like going to a trial
without any evidence.

217
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:17,650
I know I've never met that client of yours,

218
00:16:17,650 --> 00:16:20,710
but I'm just giving advice since
he seems really bad at dating.

219
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:26,530
- Good luck then.
- I'll make sure to tell him that.

220
00:17:13,670 --> 00:17:14,800
What happened?

221
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:18,990
Did I fall asleep here?

222
00:17:23,850 --> 00:17:25,220
(Jin Sim, let's meet tomorrow and talk.)

223
00:17:25,220 --> 00:17:27,910
Meet and talk?

224
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:30,210
About what?

225
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:34,240
Did I make a mistake or something?

226
00:17:34,460 --> 00:17:37,570
I've been going insane waiting
for you to ask me out.

227
00:17:37,570 --> 00:17:40,660
In my heart that is
clean, clear, and pure...

228
00:17:42,070 --> 00:17:44,000
I like you, Mr. Kwon.

229
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,040
I felt so happy.

230
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:48,050
Did you faint out of happiness?

231
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:51,270
Mr. Kwon, you're so mean!

232
00:17:56,620 --> 00:17:57,920
What will he say to me?

233
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:00,080
"I really hate women like you."

234
00:18:00,850 --> 00:18:02,490
"Let's never see each other again?"

235
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:09,800
Yun Seo, are you still sleeping?

236
00:18:12,270 --> 00:18:14,070
Hey, you were awake.

237
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:20,200
Hyuk Joon, get me a white envelope.

238
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:23,470
A white envelope? Is it a
money gift for a wedding?

239
00:18:24,980 --> 00:18:27,670
No. I won't put money in it.

240
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:30,050
- Then what?
- My letter of resignation.

241
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:33,210
- Letter of resignation?
- I won't go to work now.

242
00:18:34,790 --> 00:18:37,340
No, I can't go now.

243
00:18:42,630 --> 00:18:44,740
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

244
00:18:49,470 --> 00:18:51,480
Mr. Kwon, I'm glad to see you.

245
00:18:52,010 --> 00:18:54,110
My cousin just called me.

246
00:18:54,110 --> 00:18:56,020
He said Yun Seo can't
make it to work today.

247
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:58,410
- What?
- Why?

248
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:00,010
Is she sick?

249
00:19:00,010 --> 00:19:01,920
I don't think so. I said...

250
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:05,590
I'd bring some flowers and
porridge and go see her,

251
00:19:05,690 --> 00:19:08,560
and he said she's not sick,
but had a personal matter.

252
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:11,060
He tried to avoid talking about it.
I guess there's another reason.

253
00:19:11,060 --> 00:19:13,640
Maybe she just wants to take a day off.

254
00:19:13,660 --> 00:19:14,680
No way.

255
00:19:14,860 --> 00:19:17,380
Yun Seo didn't seem like such
an irresponsible person.

256
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:21,170
That's strange, Ms. Yang.
You're finally taking Yun Seo's side.

257
00:19:21,770 --> 00:19:23,030
I have to admit,

258
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,280
she did work very hard all this time.

259
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:27,690
She's right. At first,

260
00:19:27,780 --> 00:19:29,880
I also had a bias against her
since she's a celebrity,

261
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:31,640
but during Yoon Ha's case last time...

262
00:19:31,980 --> 00:19:35,490
and the recent Im Yun Hee Case,
she seems like a decent person.

263
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:39,180
