00:37:23,020 --> 00:37:26,900
You caught on to it, but why didn't I?

518
00:37:30,720 --> 00:37:32,530
I know you're not to blame,

519
00:37:33,490 --> 00:37:34,680
so we'll talk some other time.

520
00:37:41,930 --> 00:37:42,970
Yeo Reum!

521
00:37:42,970 --> 00:37:45,560
(Hankuk Medical Center)

522
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:47,340
She has acute gastritis
brought on by stress,

523
00:37:47,340 --> 00:37:49,040
and lethargy led to a fever.

524
00:37:49,310 --> 00:37:51,490
She'll be fine once her temperature drops.

525
00:38:07,260 --> 00:38:09,340
The case starts the day
after tomorrow, right?

526
00:38:09,860 --> 00:38:10,980
Can I see the files?

527
00:38:11,030 --> 00:38:13,000
When will we question the suspect again?

528
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:15,040
- That will be conducted tomorrow.
- I see.

529
00:38:15,130 --> 00:38:16,400
The person you have reached is unavailable.

530
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:18,110
Please leave a message...

531
00:38:35,190 --> 00:38:36,240
(Attorney Kwon Jung Rok)

532
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:40,930
Yes, Mr. Kwon. Are you here?

533
00:38:41,230 --> 00:38:44,630
I'm sorry, but we'll have
to take a rain check.

534
00:38:46,370 --> 00:38:47,490
Why?

535
00:38:49,340 --> 00:38:53,010
Prosecutor Yoo fell ill,
so I brought her to the ER.

536
00:38:53,210 --> 00:38:55,210
What happened?

537
00:38:55,340 --> 00:38:57,830
She has gastritis and a fever.

538
00:38:58,340 --> 00:39:01,780
I called another friend
to look after her today,

539
00:39:02,150 --> 00:39:04,770
but I still have to meet with the client.

540
00:39:06,020 --> 00:39:08,950
I'm afraid we won't be able to meet today.

541
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,940
I see. There's no other way, I guess.

542
00:39:12,390 --> 00:39:13,690
All right.

543
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:15,720
Sure.

544
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:33,480
What happened?

545
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,220
You fainted after talking to Jung Rok.

546
00:39:36,080 --> 00:39:37,170
Don't you remember?

547
00:39:49,860 --> 00:39:53,100
What are you doing here though?

548
00:39:54,130 --> 00:39:55,630
You finished your fluids,

549
00:39:56,700 --> 00:39:58,330
and the doctor said you can leave.

550
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:01,120
- I asked what you were doing here.
- Is that really important?

551
00:40:02,380 --> 00:40:03,870
I could ask you the same thing too.

552
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:17,720
You can't be this sensitive.

553
00:40:19,260 --> 00:40:20,860
We'll keep having trials,

554
00:40:21,060 --> 00:40:22,830
and some we'll lose.

555
00:40:22,830 --> 00:40:25,150
You can't survive if you
let them get to you.

556
00:40:27,630 --> 00:40:29,610
That's who I am though.

557
00:40:35,540 --> 00:40:36,870
I hate it.

558
00:40:39,210 --> 00:40:41,940
I hate that I crumbled after...

559
00:40:42,820 --> 00:40:44,080
losing a trial.

560
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:49,700
Also, I hate that you're...

561
00:40:51,260 --> 00:40:52,350
seeing me like this.

562
00:40:54,330 --> 00:40:55,510
I hate it too.

563
00:40:58,500 --> 00:41:00,030
I hate that this is how we are now.

564
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:05,730
Back then,

565
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:09,250
you used to be honest in front of me.

566
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:12,840
You'd laugh when you want...

567
00:41:14,580 --> 00:41:16,180
and cry when you want.

568
00:42:02,330 --> 00:42:04,140
I wonder if he's still busy.

569
00:42:04,900 --> 00:42:06,970
How could he not call me even once?

570
00:42:10,370 --> 00:42:12,040
He called. It's him.

571
00:42:15,410 --> 00:42:16,600
Yes, Mr. Kwon.

572
00:42:16,780 --> 00:42:19,460
Did I wake you up by any chance?

573
00:42:19,610 --> 00:42:20,700
No.

574
00:42:21,250 --> 00:42:22,750
Are you going home now?

575
00:42:22,820 --> 00:42:25,030
Yes. My meeting with the client
took longer than I thought.

576
00:42:25,790 --> 00:42:27,860
You must've already had dinner by now.

577
00:42:28,490 --> 00:42:30,050
Do you want to go for some tea?

578
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:31,720
Tea?

579
00:42:35,460 --> 00:42:36,480
It's okay.

580
00:42:37,100 --> 00:42:40,850
You must've had a long day,
so you should go get some rest.

581
00:42:41,030 --> 00:42:42,940
I'll see you tomorrow.

582
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,640
But Mr. Kwon...

583
00:42:46,770 --> 00:42:48,370
Yes? What is it?

584
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:52,360
I don't want today to be
our first day as a couple.

585
00:42:52,380 --> 00:42:54,450
- Sorry?
- Just listen to me.

586
00:42:54,450 --> 00:42:57,280
Who lets their first day pass
by so meaninglessly like this?

587
00:42:57,850 --> 00:42:59,350
So why don't we make...

588
00:43:00,020 --> 00:43:01,730
tomorrow our first day as a couple?

589
00:43:04,260 --> 00:43:05,340
All right.

590
00:43:05,730 --> 00:43:07,700
Then tomorrow will be our first day.

591
00:43:09,500 --> 00:43:11,910
I'm sorry I couldn't keep my promise today.

592
00:43:12,400 --> 00:43:13,630
Don't worry about it.

593
00:43:13,970 --> 00:43:17,270
Drive safely then. I'll see you tomorrow.

594
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,090
Okay.

595
00:43:28,180 --> 00:43:31,140
Okay. We've talked on the phone,
so that's enough for now.

596
00:43:41,590 --> 00:43:44,420
Alright, let's start dating
properly from tomorrow.

597
00:43:47,930 --> 00:43:49,880
Let's start dating.

598
00:43:50,340 --> 00:43:53,610
What? You want me to go
to Mr. Choi's office?

599
00:43:54,610 --> 00:43:55,730
Well...

600
00:43:56,140 --> 00:43:58,120
Can you do me this favor
for just a couple of days?

601
00:43:59,710 --> 00:44:03,120
The thing is, during this period
right after the holidays,

602
00:44:03,120 --> 00:44:05,300
the divorce rate goes up rapidly.

603
00:44:05,350 --> 00:44:07,130
Shall we call it a peak
season for divorces?

604
00:44:07,190 --> 00:44:10,420
So Mr. Choi has dozens of
divorce cases waiting...

605
00:44:10,420 --> 00:44:11,490
to be processed right now.

606
00:44:11,490 --> 00:44:14,490
And Ms. Yang is really caught
up right now helping...

607
00:44:14,590 --> 00:44:17,970
Ms. Dan with the
pharmaceutical company case.

608
00:44:18,330 --> 00:44:20,470
But, the thing is...

609
00:44:21,300 --> 00:44:24,870
if I'm not here, Mr. Kwon
will have a hard time alone.

610
00:44:25,170 --> 00:44:27,150
You just wrapped up the Im Yun Hee Case.

611
00:44:27,170 --> 00:44:29,110
Is there something you have
to take care of urgently?

612
00:44:30,610 --> 00:44:33,260
No, I guess not, at the moment.

613
00:44:34,650 --> 00:44:37,780
- I'll be fine.
- Thank you for understanding.

614
00:44:38,580 --> 00:44:41,350
And since you're the ace here,
can't you manage well on your own?

615
00:44:43,520 --> 00:44:45,120
If that's all, I'll get back to work.

616
00:44:45,120 --> 00:44:46,180
Thank you.

617
00:44:52,700 --> 00:44:54,100
I'll get going too.

618
00:44:55,430 --> 00:44:58,090
Thank you for understanding, everyone.

619
00:44:58,140 --> 00:45:00,760
I really have such considerate
employees around me.

620
00:45:07,410 --> 00:45:08,470
Hey, Jun Seok.

621
00:45:08,880 --> 00:45:11,940
Like you asked, I split up
Mr. Kwon and Yun Seo.

622
00:45:12,120 --> 00:45:13,350
Thanks, Joon Gyu.

623
00:45:14,050 --> 00:45:16,320
I'm afraid Yun Seo didn't want to...

624
00:45:16,320 --> 00:45:19,760
go to work yesterday
because of that lawyer.

625
00:45:19,790 --> 00:45:22,110
I heard from her manager, and those two...

626
00:45:22,130 --> 00:45:23,530
had many issues all this time.

627
00:45:23,530 --> 00:45:26,830
I heard Yun Seo said she'd crush
Kwon Jung Rok by all means.

628
00:45:26,830 --> 00:45:28,540
Was it that bad?

629
00:45:28,670 --> 00:45:32,270
Anyway, from now on, you should...

630
00:45:32,840 --> 00:45:36,150
recycle... No, split them up.

631
00:45:36,340 --> 00:45:37,680
Don't worry about it.

632
00:45:37,680 --> 00:45:40,200
If it's for Yun Seo's happiness,

633
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:43,410
I'll make sure those two don't
even talk to each other.

634
00:45:43,750 --> 00:45:45,720
Honey, it's me.

635
00:45:47,020 --> 00:45:50,460
I was wondering if I could
drop by during lunch.

636
00:45:52,490 --> 00:45:54,680
Oh, you're busy.

637
00:45:55,530 --> 00:45:58,520
No, it's fine. Have a good day then.

638
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:00,220
Okay.

639
00:46:01,570 --> 00:46:02,760
Ms. Dan.

640
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,900
Did you get a new boyfriend?

641
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:06,850
Yes, well...

642
00:46:07,470 --> 00:46:09,150
I did get one, but...

643
00:46:10,640 --> 00:46:13,440
But what? Why are you sighing?

644
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:14,770
- Well...
- Yes.

645
00:46:17,150 --> 00:46:19,390
Forget it. Last time, you told me...

646
00:46:19,390 --> 00:46:22,930
I had a chance with that
delivery guy, so I made a move...

647
00:46:22,990 --> 00:46:24,730
and was rejected. Don't you remember?

648
00:46:24,820 --> 00:46:26,520
I made up my mind then.

649
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:29,830
I will never receive dating
advice from you ever again.

650
00:46:30,860 --> 00:46:32,710
I'm sorry about that time.

651
00:46:33,230 --> 00:46:37,250
But there are more couples
that succeeded with my advice.

652
00:46:37,500 --> 00:46:40,140
During "Sandabang", a couple
received counseling from me...

653
00:46:40,140 --> 00:46:41,600
and expressed their feelings truthfully.

654
00:46:41,970 --> 00:46:44,080
And they ended up getting married.

655
00:46:45,110 --> 00:46:46,410
Married?

656
00:46:47,080 --> 00:46:48,680
- They got married?
- Yes.

657
00:46:49,420 --> 00:46:51,980
This is a secret, but my boyfriend is...

658
00:46:51,980 --> 00:46:54,200
the owner of the cafe
that's across the street.

659
00:46:54,790 --> 00:46:57,460
He's chic and handsome like americano,

660
00:46:57,460 --> 00:46:59,260
but his voice is smooth like a latte,

661
00:46:59,360 --> 00:47:02,490
and when he asked me out saying
he always had his eyes on me,

662
00:47:02,660 --> 00:47:04,670
it was sweet like caramel macchiato.

663
00:47:07,270 --> 00:47:08,900
That's so romantic.

664
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:11,510
So? Why are you sighing?

665
00:47:11,740 --> 00:47:13,240
Well, the problem is...

666
00:47:13,270 --> 00:47:15,690
I feel upset because it feels
like I'm the only one in love.

667
00:47:15,810 --> 00:47:18,980
I want to put all things
aside to meet him...

668
00:47:18,980 --> 00:47:20,510
and stay by his side all the time.

669
00:47:21,150 --> 00:47:22,920
But I guess he doesn't feel the same.

670
00:47:23,180 --> 00:47:24,350
Is that so?

671
00:47:24,350 --> 00:47:27,510
We were supposed to go on
a date last night too.

672
00:47:27,590 --> 00:47:29,820
But he suddenly said some
coffee beans arrived.

673
00:47:29,820 --> 00:47:33,130
He said he had to roast them,
and canceled our date.

674
00:47:33,290 --> 00:47:36,800
Just now, I told him I'd drop
by briefly during lunch,

675
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:41,150
but he said he's busy squeezing
oranges or something.

676
00:47:42,000 --> 00:47:44,670
I can understand that he's busy,

677
00:47:44,670 --> 00:47:48,490
but it seems like I'm always the
one nagging and wanting to meet.

678
00:47:49,010 --> 00:47:50,160
It's so upsetting.

679
00:47:52,240 --> 00:47:53,410
Me too.

680
00:47:55,280 --> 00:47:56,400
- What?
- What?

681
00:47:58,880 --> 00:48:02,490
I mean, if I was in your situation,

682
00:48:02,490 --> 00:48:04,700
I'd feel really upset too.

683
00:48:05,620 --> 00:48:07,730
Yun Seo, you...

684
00:48:08,560 --> 00:48:11,800
are really good at sympathizing
since you're an actress and all.

685
00:48:12,500 --> 00:48:15,970
I thought you were upset too
because you've started dating.

686
00:48:16,840 --> 00:48:19,090
That's totally ridiculous.

687
00:48:25,540 --> 00:48:27,710
Jin Sim, about yesterday's...

688
00:48:47,530 --> 00:48:50,930
Yun Seo, thanks for
volunteering to help me out.

689
00:48:51,430 --> 00:48:53,880
Since I have such high
win rates, my clients...

690
00:48:53,970 --> 00:48:55,810
come to me like moths to a flame.

691
00:48:58,140 --> 00:49:00,860
By the way, this is a table of my schedule.

692
00:49:01,770 --> 00:49:04,940
You can call the clients and
tell them when they can visit.

693
00:49:05,110 --> 00:49:06,410
Okay, I understand.

694
00:49:07,810 --> 00:49:08,870
Hold on.

695
00:49:09,980 --> 00:49:13,720
Ms. Hwang Yeon Du who's supposed
to come for counseling at 2pm.

696
00:49:13,790 --> 00:49:15,930
It's not the Hwang Yeon Du
that I know, is she?

697
00:49:16,090 --> 00:49:18,720
She probably is.
Wasn't she your rival once?

698
00:49:18,720 --> 00:49:21,480
If you're talking about
the actress, it's her.

699
00:49:23,130 --> 00:49:26,640
Oh, right. You working here
is confidential.

700
00:49:26,870 --> 00:49:29,690
Then why don't you step
out briefly later on?

701
00:49:30,440 --> 00:49:32,850
Yes, I guess I can do that.

702
00:49:34,070 --> 00:49:35,880
But is she...

703
00:49:36,710 --> 00:49:38,140
getting divorced?

704
00:49:39,340 --> 00:49:41,450
Seeing that she's coming
to me for counseling,

705
00:49:41,850 --> 00:49:42,970
I believe so.

706
00:49:43,050 --> 00:49:44,850
Why? Why is she getting divorced?

707
00:49:44,850 --> 00:49:46,580
Article 26 of the Attorneys-at-Law Act.

708
00:49:46,620 --> 00:49:49,990
"The attorney shall not disclose
any confidential information..."

709
00:49:50,020 --> 00:49:52,670
"relating to the
representation of a client."

710
00:49:55,630 --> 00:49:57,570
This is quite upsetting.

711
00:49:57,700 --> 00:49:59,500
I thought she was living
happily after getting married.

712
00:50:00,800 --> 00:50:02,610
Were you close to her?

713
00:50:04,170 --> 00:50:05,600
Close...

714
00:50:06,740 --> 00:50:08,100
my foot.

715
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:12,690
She was like my arch enemy.

716
00:50:17,050 --> 00:50:18,100
Oh Yun Seo.

717
00:50:20,320 --> 00:50:23,150
What on earth? Why did you get so tall?

718
00:50:23,860 --> 00:50:25,190
How high are your heels?

719
00:50:26,230 --> 00:50:27,690
- 7cm.
- Stylist.

720
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:31,280
- Yes?
- Bring me 10cm heels.

721
00:50:31,330 --> 00:50:33,780
No, bring me 20cm heels!

722
00:50:34,100 --> 00:50:35,120
Okay.

723
00:50:38,400 --> 00:50:40,210
- I love you.
- I love you too.

724
00:50:53,390 --> 00:50:54,570
Sir.

725
00:50:56,090 --> 00:50:58,330
Use more reflectors for my scene.

726
00:50:58,920 --> 00:51:01,070
2. No, 3 times more.

727
00:51:13,440 --> 00:51:15,720
That's the kind of person she was.

728
00:51:15,910 --> 00:51:19,350
She had to be better than me,
and she had to get treated well.

729
00:51:19,410 --> 00:51:22,580
From the very beginning of her
career until she retired,

730
00:51:22,580 --> 00:51:24,460
she really made things difficult for me.

731
00:51:25,250 --> 00:51:27,670
I suddenly don't want
to defend her anymore.

732
00:51:28,250 --> 00:51:30,060
Should I not take this case?

733
00:51:32,390 --> 00:51:33,960
That's not right.

734
00:51:34,190 --> 00:51:36,100
This is your work.

735
00:51:36,500 --> 00:51:38,800
And you're a professional.

736
00:51:39,230 --> 00:51:42,230
Then I'll just talk to her like a robot...

737
00:51:42,230 --> 00:51:43,900
that has no feelings.

738
00:51:45,470 --> 00:51:46,870
Are you here for counseling?

739
00:51:46,870 --> 00:51:49,390
Things must be very difficult for you.

740
00:51:54,010 --> 00:51:55,680
I'll even defend her in court...

741
00:51:55,680 --> 00:51:57,790
like the AlphaGo that has no soul.

742
00:51:58,250 --> 00:51:59,400
Watch carefully.

743
00:52:00,620 --> 00:52:02,930
My client...

744
00:52:03,290 --> 00:52:05,740
holds no responsibility...

745
00:52:05,920 --> 00:52:08,410
for what happened.

746
00:52:14,870 --> 00:52:16,370
My gosh, it's 1:30pm already.

747
00:52:16,370 --> 00:52:18,640
- I might run into her.
- That can't happen.

748
00:52:18,740 --> 00:52:19,840
You should go.

749
00:52:19,840 --> 00:52:21,610
I'll call you once I'm done talking to her.

750
00:52:21,640 --> 00:52:23,310
- Okay, please let me know.
- Sure.

751
00:52:24,780 --> 00:52:25,980
I'm here to meet my attorney.

752
00:52:25,980 --> 00:52:28,090
- Did you make a reservation?
- Of course.

753
00:52:40,130 --> 00:52:42,030
What are you doing?

754
00:52:42,030 --> 00:52:45,020
There's a fellow actress outside.

755
00:52:45,160 --> 00:52:47,410
You know that no one's supposed
to find out that I work here.

756
00:52:47,830 --> 00:52:48,920
Thank you.

757
00:52:51,700 --> 00:52:54,070
Then I'll pull down the blinds.

758
00:52:54,070 --> 00:52:55,600
You can stay in my office.

759
00:52:58,780 --> 00:53:00,690
No, she has the eyes of a falcon.

760
00:53:00,910 --> 00:53:02,640
It'd be better for me to just go outside.

761
00:53:06,920 --> 00:53:10,360
Hello, my name is Hwang Yeon Du.

762
00:53:10,560 --> 00:53:14,330
Hello, my name is Choi Yun Hyuk.

763
00:53:14,790 --> 00:53:16,360
- Please take a seat.
- Okay.

764
00:53:16,760 --> 00:53:19,450
I'm sure you already know me
since I used to be so famous.

765
00:53:21,230 --> 00:53:23,200
My goodness.

766
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:25,280
My designer brand wallet is
full of cash and credit cards.

767
00:53:25,600 --> 00:53:27,040
And I must've left it in the restroom.

768
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:29,650
- Please wait here for a minute.
- Sure.

769
00:53:39,450 --> 00:53:40,570
Oh Yun Seo?

770
00:53:41,220 --> 00:53:43,230
No, I'm not Oh Yun Seo.

771
00:53:43,820 --> 00:53:46,290
I must've been mistaken. I'm sorry.

772
00:53:46,290 --> 00:53:47,450
No problem.

773
00:53:52,730 --> 00:53:54,810
My goodness, what are you doing?

774
00:53:56,100 --> 00:53:58,010
See? It is you, Yun Seo.

775
00:53:58,070 --> 00:54:00,420
How dare you lie to me?

776
00:54:01,840 --> 00:54:03,850
But what are you doing here at a law firm?

777
00:54:07,680 --> 00:54:10,850
I'm here as a client.

778
00:54:10,850 --> 00:54:12,690
My goodness.

779
00:54:13,080 --> 00:54:15,600
Do you have to go to court again?

780
00:54:15,920 --> 00:54:17,080
My gosh.

781
00:54:17,720 --> 00:54:19,320
It hasn't even been that long
since you last caused a ruckus...

782
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:20,820
by going to court.

783
00:54:23,090 --> 00:54:26,230
You have such an unfortunate life.

784
00:54:26,230 --> 00:54:28,680
Shouldn't you ask a shaman
to perform an exorcism?

785
00:54:28,770 --> 00:54:30,500
Do you need some money?

786
00:54:30,500 --> 00:54:33,290
What about you? What brings you here?

787
00:54:33,470 --> 00:54:36,220
Aren't you here as a client as well?

788
00:54:38,040 --> 00:54:41,070
Why would I come to a law firm as a client?

789
00:54:41,310 --> 00:54:44,120
As you already know,
I'm being loved by my rich husband,

790
00:54:44,120 --> 00:54:46,020
and I'm living a proud and happy life.

791
00:54:46,180 --> 00:54:47,620
I'm just here...

792
00:54:49,150 --> 00:54:51,620
to take a look at the building
because I might buy it.

793
00:54:51,620 --> 00:54:55,510
I'm really interested in
buildings these days.

794
00:54:57,930 --> 00:55:00,040
I'm sorry. I feel like
I'm boasting too much.

795
00:55:01,070 --> 00:55:03,400
You won't be able to make
a comeback as an actress,

796
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:05,640
you're probably struggling financially,

797
00:55:05,770 --> 00:55:08,390
and it even seems like you got
yourself involved in a lawsuit.

798
00:55:09,110 --> 00:55:10,980
You've practically hit rock bottom.

799
00:55:11,040 --> 00:55:13,050
I think I was a bit too harsh on you.

800
00:55:14,410 --> 00:55:15,470
Yun Seo.

801
00:55:17,150 --> 00:55:18,340
Go home safely.

802
00:55:18,620 --> 00:55:21,270
Make sure the reporters
don't take photos of you.

803
00:55:23,150 --> 00:55:25,590
Or do the reporters not
care about you anymore?

804
00:55:25,590 --> 00:55:26,610
Yeon Du!

805
00:55:26,660 --> 00:55:28,090
My gosh.

806
00:55:28,190 --> 00:55:31,390
It's like she was born to harass me.

807
00:55:31,400 --> 00:55:34,970
One time, I had a dress picked out
for an awards ceremony,

808
00:55:34,970 --> 00:55:37,350
but she took it from me
and wore it herself.

809
00:55:38,440 --> 00:55:40,470
And another time, she went to see
the director that cast me...

810
00:55:40,470 --> 00:55:42,450
as the main character of his drama.

811
00:55:42,770 --> 00:55:44,370
Then she told him that she
can do better than me...

812
00:55:44,440 --> 00:55:46,720
and that she'll even get paid less than me.

813
00:55:46,950 --> 00:55:49,220
So eventually, she ended up getting
the role of the main character.

814
00:55:49,510 --> 00:55:50,540
My gosh.

815
00:55:51,380 --> 00:55:55,060
That drama incident still makes angry.

816
00:55:55,320 --> 00:55:59,300
Mr. Kwon, is it too late
to file a lawsuit on this?

817
00:56:00,290 --> 00:56:02,130
Yes, it's too late.

818
00:56:02,560 --> 00:56:03,620
What?

819
00:56:03,830 --> 00:56:06,100
In order for it to be an obstruction
of business or an illegal act,

820
00:56:06,100 --> 00:56:08,550
she had to spread false information
or make you get fired unfairly.

821
00:56:08,970 --> 00:56:11,110
But what she did was merely
making a better offer...

822
00:56:11,340 --> 00:56:13,720
by offering the director
to get paid less than you.

823
00:56:14,010 --> 00:56:15,850
She wasn't being deceptive or unfair.

824
00:56:20,610 --> 00:56:24,460
Gosh, you are very logical.

825
00:56:26,280 --> 00:56:27,310
Pardon?

826
00:56:29,090 --> 00:56:31,710
I was just complaining to my boyfriend.

827
00:56:33,530 --> 00:56:36,900
But I actually thought I was getting
counseling from an attorney.

828
00:56:41,000 --> 00:56:44,100
If you ever tell me that
someone was mean to you,

829
00:56:44,100 --> 00:56:47,100
I feel like I'd take your side
regardless of who did what.

830
00:56:47,110 --> 00:56:49,720
And I feel like I'd
really hate that person.

831
00:56:51,410 --> 00:56:53,320
But you must not feel that way.

832
00:56:58,850 --> 00:56:59,900
That's not it.

833
00:57:00,890 --> 00:57:02,070
Also...

834
00:57:03,820 --> 00:57:04,980
Never mind.

835
00:57:29,110 --> 00:57:31,290
I'll be off now.

836
00:57:32,950 --> 00:57:35,670
And I'm really sorry to say this,

837
00:57:36,520 --> 00:57:38,760
but I don't want today to
be our first day either.

838
00:57:59,060 --> 00:58:02,530
I'm sorry, but we'll have
to take a rain check.

839
00:58:02,530 --> 00:58:03,930
There's no other way, I guess.

840
00:58:04,440 --> 00:58:05,670
All right.

841
00:58:06,200 --> 00:58:09,540
She did sound a little down that day.

842
00:58:10,840 --> 00:58:13,460
You want me to go to Mr. Choi's office?

843
00:58:13,580 --> 00:58:15,040
No, I guess not, at the moment.

844
00:58:15,750 --> 00:58:16,840
I'll be fine.

845
00:58:19,120 --> 00:58:21,670
And she did seem a little upset then.

846
00:58:23,120 --> 00:58:26,080
But I only agreed to that for her sake...

847
00:58:26,990 --> 00:58:29,030
because it'd be better for her
to experience various cases.

848
00:58:44,040 --> 00:58:46,080
Does he even like me at all?

849
00:58:57,690 --> 00:58:58,740
My gosh.

850
00:58:59,660 --> 00:59:02,290
Mr. Kwon, what are you doing here?

851
00:59:02,290 --> 00:59:03,760
Your cell phone was turned off.

852
00:59:05,230 --> 00:59:06,460
Is it turned off?

853
00:59:09,570 --> 00:59:11,380
Is that why you came?

854
00:59:11,900 --> 00:59:14,050
- To tell me that?
- No.

855
00:59:15,110 --> 00:59:17,460
- Let's go on a date.
- What?

856
00:59:18,580 --> 00:59:19,700
A date?

857
00:59:26,750 --> 00:59:29,370
What's going on all of a sudden?

858
00:59:29,490 --> 00:59:32,250
I really didn't think we
should delay another day.

859
00:59:33,730 --> 00:59:35,470
I don't want to put it off anymore.

860
00:59:35,860 --> 00:59:37,600
Let's make today our first day.

861
00:59:41,800 --> 00:59:43,030
That's what I'd like to do.

862
00:59:44,070 --> 00:59:45,670
- Do you not feel the same way?
- No, I'd love to.

863
00:59:51,180 --> 00:59:52,710
Let's go, then.

864
00:59:53,710 --> 00:59:56,300
Where are we going?

865
01:00:09,430 --> 01:00:11,200
I've never been to an observatory before.

866
01:00:11,760 --> 01:00:13,730
How did you think of this place?

867
01:00:13,730 --> 01:00:15,640
It was too late to go anywhere,

868
01:00:15,700 --> 01:00:17,200
and we couldn't have our first date...

869
01:00:17,200 --> 01:00:18,630
at a 24-hour pork backbone stew restaurant.

870
01:00:19,170 --> 01:00:22,000
The location had to be
special but not crowded.

871
01:00:22,210 --> 01:00:24,050
I weighed my options...

872
01:00:24,240 --> 01:00:25,940
and came up with a place...

873
01:00:25,980 --> 01:00:27,070
decent enough to go on a date on at night.

874
01:00:27,850 --> 01:00:28,900
Do you like it?

875
01:00:29,010 --> 01:00:30,030
I love it.

876
01:00:30,550 --> 01:00:31,950
It's the best.

877
01:00:34,150 --> 01:00:36,980
It must be easier to spot stars over there.

878
01:00:36,990 --> 01:00:38,250
Let's go.

879
01:00:50,130 --> 01:00:51,220
A shooting star!

880
01:00:53,400 --> 01:00:54,490
Did you see it?

881
01:00:55,470 --> 01:00:56,660
No, I didn't.

882
01:00:57,740 --> 01:00:58,910
My gosh.

883
01:00:59,840 --> 01:01:02,330
You should've been right behind me.

884
01:01:02,480 --> 01:01:03,980
Why do you walk so slow?

885
01:01:08,850 --> 01:01:11,510
Why are you looking at me like that?

886
01:01:11,920 --> 01:01:14,240
Because I'm sorry.

887
01:01:14,890 --> 01:01:15,950
What?

888
01:01:16,590 --> 01:01:18,090
Jin Sim,

889
01:01:19,230 --> 01:01:21,340
I'm sorry that I'm on the slow side.

890
01:01:21,730 --> 01:01:25,480
This isn't anything to
apologize about though.

891
01:01:25,640 --> 01:01:29,280
I thought about my actions,

892
01:01:30,780 --> 01:01:32,620
and I was inattentive.

893
01:01:32,880 --> 01:01:34,340
It took me a long time to ask you out...

894
01:01:34,580 --> 01:01:36,210
and I canceled our first date.

895
01:01:36,780 --> 01:01:39,370
I kept upsetting you in a lot of ways.

896
01:01:41,320 --> 01:01:44,250
It's all because I'm awkward
at expressing my feelings.

897
01:01:45,760 --> 01:01:49,460
I feel bad that my ineptness
is the cause of it.

898
01:01:51,560 --> 01:01:53,190
I tend to be slow,

899
01:01:54,170 --> 01:01:57,510
so I might not be able to match your pace.

900
01:01:59,270 --> 01:02:01,920
However, I'll take steps towards you...

901
01:02:02,440 --> 01:02:04,420
at my own pace though.

902
01:02:06,950 --> 01:02:09,200
Slowly and but for a long time.

903
01:02:28,770 --> 01:02:30,810
Actually, Mr. Kwon,

904
01:02:32,700 --> 01:02:35,700
could I ask you something?

905
01:02:45,820 --> 01:02:48,650
Do you like me?

906
01:02:53,660 --> 01:02:54,680
Sorry?

907
01:02:55,760 --> 01:02:59,610
It's nothing. Forget you heard anything.

908
01:03:22,350 --> 01:03:23,580
I like you.

909
01:03:26,060 --> 01:03:29,630
I like you, Jin Sim.

910
01:03:30,960 --> 01:03:32,020
A lot.

911
01:03:42,760 --> 01:03:46,290
♫ <i>I'm looking at you for a while</i> ♫

912
01:03:46,290 --> 01:03:52,170
♫ <i>Wondering if you feel the same way</i> ♫

913
01:03:52,170 --> 01:03:55,690
♫ <i>Of course, I really don't know</i> ♫

914
01:03:55,690 --> 01:03:59,960
♫ <i>It's still so hard</i> ♫

915
01:04:00,000 --> 01:04:05,260
♫ <i>My heart has slow footsteps</i> ♫

916
01:04:05,260 --> 01:04:10,210
♫ <i>So with all my strength,
I chased after you</i> ♫

917
01:04:10,210 --> 01:04:13,660
♫ <i>Each step I take</i> ♫

918
01:04:13,710 --> 01:04:18,960
♫ <i>You're right there
so why am I hesitating?</i> ♫

919
01:04:18,960 --> 01:04:28,220
♫ <i>Oh love, love is, what is it, what is love?</i> ♫

920
01:04:28,260 --> 01:04:32,090
♫ <i>Oh love</i> ♫

921
01:04:32,990 --> 01:04:34,900
(Touch Your Heart)

922
01:04:35,630 --> 01:04:38,210
Ms. Oh will have men
vying for her attention,

923
01:04:38,400 --> 01:04:39,890
so do better if you wish to keep her.

924
01:04:39,960 --> 01:04:40,990
Let's get back to work.

925
01:04:41,330 --> 01:04:43,070
Wait, are you...

926
01:04:43,100 --> 01:04:45,000
- jealous?
- Of course not.

927
01:04:45,000 --> 01:04:47,040
She used to be very popular.

928
01:04:47,070 --> 01:04:48,910
Her commercials aired all the time.

929
01:04:48,940 --> 01:04:51,430
She sure is a goddess.

930
01:04:53,110 --> 01:04:54,580
I'll try being with Ms. Oh then.

931
01:04:54,880 --> 01:04:57,330
I wonder what kind of men she'll date.

932
01:04:57,980 --> 01:04:59,990
There's no way it's Mr. Kwon.

933
01:05:01,020 --> 01:05:03,750
I want to be the one who makes you laugh.

934
01:05:04,260 --> 01:05:06,840
Mr. Kwon, can we...

935
01:05:08,030 --> 01:05:09,360
kiss?

936
01:05:09,990 --> 01:05:11,180
Here?

